\begin_layout Proposition
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop:MA Cord Pol"

\end_inset

El momento angular en coordenadas polares viene dado por la expresión:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vec{L}_{O}=mr^{2}\dot{\theta}\hat{k}
\]

\end_inset

donde 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{k}=\hat{r}\times\hat{\theta}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Nótese que:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dot{\vec{r}}=\dot{r}\hat{r}+r\dot{\theta}\hat{\theta}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Así, aplicando la definición de momento angular de una partícula (ver definición
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand vref
reference "def:L"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

), tenemos:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vec{L}_{O}=m\vec{r}\times\dot{\vec{r}}=m\vec{r}\times\left(\dot{r}\hat{r}+r\dot{\theta}\hat{\theta}\right)=m\dot{r}\underbrace{\vec{r}\times\hat{r}}_{=\vec{0}}+mr\dot{\theta}\underbrace{\vec{r}\times\hat{\theta}}_{=\hat{k}}=mr^{2}\dot{\theta}\hat{k}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Corollary
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "cor:thetapunto función L"

\end_inset

