\begin_inset Formula $\dot{\theta}$
\end_inset

 y la velocidad 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{\theta}$
\end_inset

 en el eje 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\theta}$
\end_inset

 (el perpendicular al radial) en función del momento angular:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{matrix}{\displaystyle \dot{\theta}=\frac{L_{O}}{mr^{2}}} &  & {\displaystyle v_{\theta}=\frac{L_{O}}{mr}}\end{matrix}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Partimos de la proposición anterior:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
L_{O}=mr^{2}\dot{\theta}\Leftrightarrow\dot{\theta}=\frac{L_{O}}{mr^{2}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Por otra parte:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
mr^{2}\dot{\theta}=mrv_{\theta}
\]

\end_inset

Así que:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
mrv_{\theta}=L_{O}\Leftrightarrow v_{\theta}=\frac{L_{O}}{mr}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

