\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop:Transfer Ener"

\end_inset

Sean dos partículas con masa 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{1}$
\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{2}$
\end_inset

 que colisionan elásticamente.
 La proporción de energía transferida al blanco viene dado por la expresión:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{T_{2,f}}{T}=\frac{4m_{1}m_{2}}{M^{2}}\sin^{2}\frac{\theta^{*}}{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Partimos de las proposiciones 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand vref
reference "prop:Ener Trans Blanco"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand vref
reference "prop:Ener Total"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 De manera que:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{T_{2,f}}{T}=\frac{\frac{2p^{*\,2}}{m_{2}}\sin^{2}\frac{\theta^{*}}{2}}{\frac{M^{2}p^{*\,2}}{2m_{1}m_{2}^{2}}}=\frac{2p^{*\,2}\sin^{2}\frac{\theta^{*}}{2}2m_{1}m_{2}^{2}}{M^{2}p^{*\,2}m_{2}}=\frac{4m_{1}m_{2}}{M^{2}}\sin^{2}\frac{\theta^{*}}{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

